*+
*  Name:
*     SEC_PAR

*  Purpose:
*     Define SEC system parameter constants.

*  Language:
*     Starlink Fortran 77

*  Type of Module:
*     Global constants include file.

*  Description:
*     This file defines the size of any SECTOR global constants.

*  Authors:
*     GJP: Grant Privett (STARLINK)
*     {enter_new_authors_here}

*  History:
*     16-NOV-1992 (GJP):
*        Original version.
*     {enter_further_changes_here}

*  Bugs:
*     {note_any_bugs_here}

*-

*  Global constants:

*  The maximum size of the results arrays.
      INTEGER SEC__RESUL
      PARAMETER ( SEC__RESUL = 4096 )

*  The value of the geometric constant PI.
      REAL SEC__PIVAL
      PARAMETER ( SEC__PIVAL = 3.1415926 )

*  The value of the geometric constant needed to convert radians to
*  degrees format.
      REAL SEC__RADS
      PARAMETER ( SEC__RADS = 1./2./SEC__PIVAL*360. )

*  A very small value that is greater than 0.0. The actual
*  value is not important.
      REAL SEC__VSMAL
      PARAMETER ( SEC__VSMAL = 1.E-20 )
